 {"id":"franken_networkx-201f","title":"parity: DiGraph and MultiDiGraph succ should return read-only adjacency views","description":"DiGraph.succ and MultiDiGraph.succ currently expose raw mutable neighbor dicts instead of NetworkX's read-only AtlasView/AdjacencyView wrappers. In FrankenNetworkX, assigning G.succ['a']['x'] = {} is silently accepted and leaves the graph unchanged, while upstream NetworkX raises TypeError. Match the upstream successor-mapping contract on directed graph families.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T08:42:30.201281327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T08:42:30.201281327Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
